    "In Table I and Figure 1, we compare our method to the baselines, ranking methods by their evaluation scores and estimating data distribution by kernel density estimation (KDE).",
    "We also visualize real and generated time-series samples onto a latent space using t-SNE [16] in Figure 3.",
    "Our proposed method shows the best generation quality in most of the cases.",
    "Furthermore, the t-SNE and KDE visualization results provide intuitive evidence that our method's generation diversity is also superior to that of the baselines.",
    "Our contributions are summarized as follows:1) We, for the first time, propose an SGM-based universal time-series synthesis method."
